        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>tempera [300015062], water-base paint [300183946], paint by composition or origin [300015030], paint (coating) [300015029], coating by form [300015002], coating (material) [300014907], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artist's material consisting of pigments ground in an emulsion medium in which the oily ingredient is linseed oil, stand oil, or most often, a mixture of stand oil and damar varnish; emulsified with gum arabic solution and glycerin.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026701/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Material artístico que consiste en pigmentos molidos en un medio de emulsión en el cual el ingrediente oleoso es aceite de linaza, aceite de linaza hervido y, más frecuentemente, una mezcla de aceite de linaza hervido y barniz damar, emulsionada con solución de goma arábica y glicerina.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schildersmateriaal bestaande uit gemalen pigmenten in een emulsiedrager waarvan het olieachtige bestanddeel lijnolie of standolie is, of meestal een mengsel van standolie en damarvernis; geëmulgeerd met een Arabische gomoplossing en glycerine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種繪畫顏料，將顏料磨碎在乳狀媒材中製成，其油性材料為亞麻籽油、熟油，或者更常見為熟油與丹瑪漆的混合物。與阿拉伯膠溶液及甘油一起乳化。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
